thread.title: SEE IT: Kim Kardashian’s Paris robbery photos released
thread.title_full: SEE IT: Kim Kardashian’s Paris robbery photos released

author: KATE FELDMAN
title: SEE IT: Kim Kardashian’s Paris robbery photos released
text:
6:10 PM 
Crime scene photos of Kim Kardashian’s harrowing Paris robbery tell a scary story. 
The images, released by France’s TF1 news channel , show Kardashian’s hotel bedroom and bathroom, as well as what appears to be the tape used to bind her hands and a gag. 
Surveillance video also shows the suspects likely staking out the building before the robbery. 
The “Keeping Up with the Kardashians” star was bound and gagged on Oct. 3 in Paris and robbed of more than $5 million worth of jewelry — including her $4 million 20-karat Lorraine Schwartz emerald cut diamond engagement ring. Crime scene photos of tape used to bind the hands of Kim Kardashian, shown here a day before her Paris robbery, and a gag were released Sunday. (Marc Piasecki/GC Images) 
Seventeen people were arrested in January in connection with the crime. 
Seven were released, four were indicted on Jan. 12 for charges including robbery, kidnapping and being in an organized gang and the other six were charged on Jan. 13. 
In early February, Kardashian met with French investigators in New York to discuss the details of the attack.
